text.__SUMMARY__: Conus alexandrinus is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.
text.Description: The size of the shell varies between 18 mm and 34 mm.
text.Distribution: This species occurs in the Atlantic Ocean off Angola.

Rolán E. & Röckel D. 2000. The endemic Conus of Angola. Argonauta 13(2): 5-44, 150 figs.
